  "bug_info": "Summary of configuration for Project: JacksonXml\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    Script dir: /root/defects4j/framework\n      Base dir: /root/defects4j\n    Major root: /root/defects4j/major\n      Repo dir: /root/defects4j/project_repos\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    Project ID: JacksonXml\n       Program: jackson-dataformat-xml\n    Build file: /root/defects4j/framework/projects/JacksonXml/JacksonXml.build.xml\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n           Vcs: Vcs::Git\n    Repository: /root/defects4j/project_repos/jackson-dataformat-xml.git\n     Commit db: /root/defects4j/framework/projects/JacksonXml/active-bugs.csv\nNumber of bugs: 6\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSummary for Bug: JacksonXml-3\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nRevision ID (fixed version):\n79a4b57f2bbe08ce46e6dabb0a8b76f4a787141c\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nRevision date (fixed version):\n2016-08-18 15:07:01 -0700\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nBug report id:\n204\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nBug report url:\nhttps://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-dataformat-xml/issues/204\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nRoot cause in triggering tests:\n - com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat.xml.stream.XmlParserNextXxxTest::testXmlAttributesWithNextTextValue\n   --> junit.framework.ComparisonFailure: expected:<7> but was:<null>\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nList of modified sources:\n - com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat.xml.deser.FromXmlParser\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------",
  "bug_report_content": "Title: FromXMLParser nextTextValue() incorrect for attributes\nState: closed\n\nDescription:\nAs of #129 the Method nextTextValue of FromXMLParser will no longer return a value for attributes. As the _currToken is JsonToken.VALUE_STRING in this case I think it is wrong to return null and it should return _currText.\n\nComments:\n\n[cowtowncoder]: Quite possible. Do you have a simple reproduction to show the problem, and to make sure fix would resolve the problem.\n\n[frederikz]: Modified test from XmlParserTest:\n\n```\npublic void testXmlAttributesWithNextTextValue() throws Exception\n    {\n        final String XML = \"<data max=\\\"7\\\" offset=\\\"9\\\"/>\";\n\n        FromXmlParser xp = (FromXmlParser) _xmlFactory.createParser(new StringReader(XML));\n\n        // First: verify handling without forcing array handling:\n        assertToken(JsonToken.START_OBJECT, xp.nextToken()); // <data>\n        assertToken(JsonToken.FIELD_NAME, xp.nextToken()); // <max>\n        assertEquals(\"max\", xp.getCurrentName());\n        assertEquals(\"7\", xp.nextTextValue());\n\n        assertToken(JsonToken.FIELD_NAME, xp.nextToken()); // <offset>\n        assertEquals(\"offset\", xp.getCurrentName());\n\n        StringWriter w = new StringWriter();\n        assertEquals(6, xp.getText(w));\n        assertEquals(\"offset\", w.toString());\n\n        assertEquals(\"9\", xp.nextTextValue());\n\n        w = new StringWriter();\n        assertEquals(1, xp.getText(w));\n        assertEquals(\"9\", w.toString());\n\n        assertToken(JsonToken.END_OBJECT, xp.nextToken()); // </data>\n        xp.close();\n    }\n```\n\n[cowtowncoder]: @frederikz  Forgot to ask which versions this is with?\n\n[cowtowncoder]: Was occurring at least with 2.7 and 2.8; and since earlier branches not maintained any more bit of a moot point. Fix will be in 2.7.7 / 2.8.2; was a simple case of not actually returning the text...\n\nThank you for reporting this!",
